extract: The Zanesville Potters were a minor league baseball team based in Zanesville, Ohio. The "Potters" played as members of the Class B level Central League from 1910 to 1912. In 1913, the "Zanesville Flood Sufferers" briefly continued minor league play in the Interstate League, before the team disbanded in June 1913. The 1913 Zanesville team was named for a major 1913 flood that affected Zanesville. The flood occurred just months after a tornado hit the town in 1912.
